util.function

Class Expected<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.function.Expected<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the expected value
    E - the type of the unexpected error value

    public final class Expected<T,E>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Expected class provides some other kind of error handling compared to Exception. Instead of returning the result in the case of success and throwing an exception in the case of failure, Expected objects can be created of results by calling expected(Object) and error values by calling unexpected(Object) function.
    Author:
    roehrdor

      • map

        public <U> Expected<U,E> map(java.util.function.Function<? super T,? extends U> mapper)
                      throws java.lang.NullPointerException

        If the expected value is present and the provided mapper is not null, the mapping function will be applied to the contained value. The return value of the mapper will be wrapped into an Expected by calling the expected(Object) function.

        If the mapper is null a NullPointerException will be thrown. If the value does not exist an Expected with the unexpected value will be returned.

        Type Parameters:
        U - the type of the result of the mapping function
        Parameters:
        mapper - mapping function to be applied if not null and value exists
        Returns:
        an Expected containing the result of the mapper or if the value does not exist an Expected of the contained error value
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the mapper is null

      • bind

        public <U> U bind(java.util.function.Function<? super T,? extends U> binder)

        If the expected value is present and the provided binder is not null, the mapping function will be applied to the contained value. The return value of the binder will be returned without being wrapped into an Expected

        If the binder is null a NullPointerException will be thrown. If the value does not exist null will be returned

        Type Parameters:
        U - the return type of the binding function
        Parameters:
        binder - binding function to be applied if not null and value exists
        Returns:
        the result of the applied binding function or null if no value does exist
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the binder is null

      • bindExpected

        public <U> Expected<U,E> bindExpected(java.util.function.Function<? super T,? extends Expected<U,E>> binder)

        If the expected value is present and the provided binder is not null, the mapping function will be applied to the contained value. The return value of the binder will be returned as Expected.

        If the binder is null a NullPointerException will be thrown. If the value does exist an Expected with the already contained error value will be returned.

        Type Parameters:
        U - the value type of the binding function
        Parameters:
        binder - binding function to be applied if not null and value exists
        Returns:
        the result of the applied binding function or an Expected with the already contained unexpected value if no value is present
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the binder is null
